    WHY DOES SATAN HATE MANKIND?
    Because of the scarcity of information that the scriptures reveal concerning this topic, this paper can only be speculative and not dogmatic. Although speculative, this does not mean that the statements contained herein are without scriptural support.  It is only an admission that the Bible is not explicit in describing the events that predate man’s historical existence.  However, the Bible does provide us with enough evidence to implicitly make some very interesting conclusions. The following comments are submitted to the reader as a plausible answer to the question posed by the title of this paper.
    We have often heard it taught that it was Lucifer’s pride which prompted his rebellion against God. While pride is a definite character flaw of Lucifer, it was not this element in itself which caused him to rebel——- it was jealousy.  Pride was the “vehicle” which gave impetus to jealousy.  One can only have pride in that which he possesses, or at least, believes he possesses. Whereas, one becomes jealous over that which he does not pos sess.  Lust or jealousy will eventually cause one to resort to take that which he desires by force. We find this principle in James 4:1,2.
    “From whence come wars and fightings among you? come they not hence, even of your lusts that war in vour members? Ye lust, and have not: (therefore) ye kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: (therefore) ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not.”
    The inserted “therefore” gives justice to the Greek text which emphasizes the causative agent for the action verbs.
    This is exactly what Lucifer attempted. He was not content with the glory and beauty which was given him, instead he desired the glory which only God possessed.
    We find some very illuminating comments concerning Lucifer in Isaiah 14 and Ezekiel 28. Although these passages have a historical fulfillment in the kings of Babylon and Tyrus, the pride and glory of these kings/
    /”
    cities are reminiscent to that exhibited by Lucifer prior to his fall.
