    (6) Thou wast perfect.  Here again, the modifiers emphasize the ultimate of God’s creation.
    (7) Corrupted thy wisdom by reason of thy brightness.  Lucifer’s name means “light-bearing”.  I believe God gave Lucifer a glory, an aura of light, which was similar to God’s own radiance (1 John 1:5; 1 Tim.6:16; James 1:17) except on a much diminuated scale. No other angel received this glory, else Lucifer ’s name would have no unique significance.  One might object to this theory, however, in consideration of 2 Cor.11:14:
