    The second point we will consider reinforces the first.  According to Strong’s Exhaustive Concordance, the word “present” (â»3320) means “to place [anything so as to stay]”.  This denotes permanency.  The word was first used with the “sons of God” in Job 1:6, but with boththe “sons of God” and Satan in Job 2:1.
    The question may now arise whether or not Satan still has this privilege granted to him.  The answer is an emphatic No!  When then was this right revoked? Satan lost all hopes of ever regaining his lofty position at Jesus’ first advent. Not only was Jesus the victor in his desert tempta tion and at his resurrection, but the victors crown was even passed on to his disciples.
